  "title": "Maintenance Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will perform preventive maintenance and repairs on waste storage equipment to ensure smooth operations. You will respond quickly to emergencies, maintain accurate records, and support machine operators through training and troubleshooting.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform scheduled preventive maintenance and servicing on waste storage equipment to reduce breakdowns and extend equipment lifespan</li><li>Troubleshoot and repair machinery promptly to minimize downtime and maintain operational efficiency</li><li>Respond quickly to emergency maintenance requests and equipment breakdowns to restore functionality</li><li>Assist in repair work and escalate support calls when needed, including during weekends and public holidays</li><li>Follow standard operating procedures (SOPs) and safety regulations to maintain a safe work environment for all staff</li><li>Maintain accurate records of maintenance activities, repairs, and inspections for reporting and compliance purposes</li><li>Prepare monthly maintenance and service reports to track equipment performance and identify areas for improvement</li><li>Provide training to machine operators to improve equipment handling and reduce faults</li><li>Carry out other ad-hoc tasks as assigned to support maintenance operations</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/NITEC / Higher NITEC in Mechanical, Electrical, or equivalent</li><li>Valid Singapore Class 3 Driving Licence</li><li>Apply basic knowledge of mechanical and electrical systems to perform maintenance and repairs effectively</li><li>Read and interpret machine manuals and safety instructions to ensure accurate servicing</li><li>Maintain physical fitness to perform hands-on maintenance work safely and efficiently</li><li>Use commercial software applications proficiently to maintain records and reports</li><li>Be willing to be on standby for emergency calls after office hours, weekends, and public holidays</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Conversational ability in Japanese (advantageous for communication but not essential)</li></ul>",
